<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "7B">
<servcat sctnbr = "07" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A7206041" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Compressor Drive Belt Inspection and Adjustment
</title>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A7206041001">
<title>
Inspection
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Check compressor drive belt (1) for wear, cracks, deformation and contamination. If any defect is found, replace the belt with new one. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A7206042"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Check compressor drive belt tension by measuring how much it deflects when pushed at intermediate point between magnetic clutch pulley (2) and crankshaft pulley (3) with about 100 N (10 kg) force after rotating crankshaft pulley 360&#176;. If belt tension is out of specification, adjust belt tension referring to “Adjustment”.
</ptxt>
<spec-sdm>
<sdm-title>
Compressor drive belt tension
</sdm-title>
<sdm-part>
“a”
</sdm-part>
<sdm1>
<sdm-condition>
Belt in use
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
8.0 – 9.0 mm (0.32 – 0.35 in.) / 100 N (10 kgf or 22 lb)
</sdm-value>
<sdm-ptxt>
 between Magnet clutch pulley and Crankshaft pulley
</sdm-ptxt>
</sdm1>
<sdm1>
<sdm-condition>
New belt
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
6.5 – 7.5 mm (0.26 – 0.29 in.) / 100 N (10 kgf or 22 lb)
</sdm-value>
<sdm-ptxt>
 between Magnet clutch pulley and Crankshaft pulley
</sdm-ptxt>
</sdm1>
</spec-sdm>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B720014.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.502mm" ver = "02" gw = "184" gh = "146"/>
</figure>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A7206041002">
<title>
Adjustment
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Loosen tension pulley nut (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Adjust belt tension by tightening or loosening tension pulley adjusting bolt (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten tension pulley nut to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T7B005">
<t-part>
Tension pulley nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
60
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
6.1
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
44.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten tension pulley adjusting bolt to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T7B006">
<t-part>
Tension pulley adjusting bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
10
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.0
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
7.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Rotate crankshaft pulley clockwise 360&#176;, and then recheck drive belt (3) tension.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A720017.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "74.497mm" ver = "02" gw = "186" gh = "195"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
